themselves faced bankruptcy.

00:17:16.455 --> 00:17:19.390 align:middle line:84%
The people began to
realize far reaching

00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:23.634 align:middle line:84%
corruption and the breakdown
of the old structures.

00:17:23.634 --> 00:17:26.950 align:middle line:84%
The structures that were
meant to be our foundation

00:17:26.950 --> 00:17:31.420 align:middle line:84%
were not supporting the whole,
and people either rose up

00:17:31.420 --> 00:17:35.520 align:middle line:84%
or sunk into dismay
and depression.

00:17:35.520 --> 00:17:39.000 align:middle line:84%
Disillusion tends to be
an introspective stage.

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:41.190 align:middle line:84%
It's an opportunity
to reflect on what

00:17:41.190 --> 00:17:44.010 align:middle line:90%
is at the root of the issue.

00:17:44.010 --> 00:17:46.050 align:middle line:84%
It's one thing to be
angry, and another thing

00:17:46.050 --> 00:17:48.630 align:middle line:90%
to look at what's the cause.

00:17:48.630 --> 00:17:50.160 align:middle line:84%
And at this point,
people started

00:17:50.160 --> 00:17:52.920 align:middle line:84%
to look at the cause
and effect and seek out

00:17:52.920 --> 00:17:57.360 align:middle line:84%
actions to reorient
us in a new direction.

00:17:57.360 --> 00:18:01.080 align:middle line:84%
Eventually, we saw the rise
of social media platforms,

00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:05.630 align:middle line:84%
with Facebook coming onto the
scene in 2004, YouTube in 2005,

00:18:05.630 --> 00:18:07.980 align:middle line:90%
